03/12/2008
NICOSIA, Cyprus -- President Demetris Christofias and Turkish Cypriot leader Mehmet Ali Talat met again on Tuesday (December 2nd) in a bid to reunify the long-divided island.
The meeting was the 11th since the launch of direct talks in September under UN auspices.
This round focused on governance in the future federal state, said Taye-Brook Zerihoun, the UN special representative in Cyprus.
(Xinhua, Phileleftheros - 02/12/08)
